FBIS3-42325 "jptot007__l94003" JPRS-TOT-94-007-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 16 February 1994 SELECTED VIDEO REPORTS SELECTED VIDEO REPORTS 11111111 11111111 Article Type:CSO The following list includes terrorism-related video reports extracted from FBIS Video Program Summaries from 5 to 10 February, ordered alphabetically by country. Each entry is prefaced by the name of the city where the report originated, followed by the FBIS TV Center order number (e.g., BOG 94-001) and the date of broadcast. Tapes may be ordered by calling 1-800-822-5115 for subscribers in Virginia and 1-800-542-8660 for those outside Virginia. Tapes are available for 30 days and are for U.S. Government official use only. Colombia Bogota BOG 94-051 (8 Feb)--Report on bombings of three political party headquarters in Santander, two in Risaralda. Bogota BOG 94-051 (8 Feb)--Report on arrest of ELN Medellin militia leader Eddy Oswaldo Ruiz Carvajal and 46 others. Clips show weapons, ammunition. Egypt/Libya Tripoli TRI 94-038 (7 Feb)--Excerpted clips of Egyptian President Mubarak's speech on terrorism before army officers, followed by excerpts from al-Qadhdhafi speech commenting on terrorism in Egypt, other countries. Iran Algiers ALG 94-036 (5 Feb)--Coach, three soldiers kidnapped. Havana HAV 94-034 (8 Feb)--Report on 20 men arrested on charges of attempting to assassinate president of Iran. Israel/Palestinians Tripoli TRI 94-037 (6 Feb)--Israeli court sentences three Palestinians to life for killing four Israelis. South Africa Johannesburg JOH 94-037 (5 Feb)--Report on sabotage damage to power pylons, rail lines in western Transvaal. Johannesburg JOH 94-039 (7 Feb)--Report on right- and left-wingers arrested for bombings and attacks in western Transvaal, Orange Free State, eastern Cape, Natal (2 min). Second report on armed attack on Richmond homestead (1 min). Johannesburg JOH 94-041 (9 Feb)--Police arrest five more in connection with explosions in Orange Free State and western Transvaal (1 min). Spain Madrid MAD 94-037 (7 Feb)--ETA kills army colonel in Barcelona. Madrid MAD 94-039 (9 Feb)--French authorities arrest "key" ETA member. Tajikistan Moscow MOS 94-5110 (8 Feb)--Report on release of unspecified "terrorists." United Kingdom/Spain London LIT 94-019 (8 Feb)--English-language broadcast. Analytical report comparing Irish Republican Army and Spanish separatist group ETA. Video shows car bomb detonating in London, several various scenes of bomb damage, interviews with people who claim to have been beaten by Spanish authorities to extract information from them on ETA, commentaries by Spanish officials (3.5 min.). Former Yugoslavia Belgrade BEL 94-033 (9 Feb)--Belgrade viewers have recognized man shown in Bosnia-Hercegovina TV interview as a known explosives expert. Footage shows "Sky TV" interview with man, man fleeing by car.
